Topics:

1) Commerce and consumer protection. Grammar: partitive (singular and plural), impersonal voice (past tense).
2) Household chemistry and garbage. Grammar: declination of cardinal numerals, participle.
3) School and education. Grammar: compound and complec sentences, word order in a sentence.
4) Health and lifespan. Grammar: verb government, transitive and intransitive verbs.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Designed as a preparation course for the National Advanced Estonian Language Test (C1), the course aims at providing students with the necessary skills and strategies required to pass the test successfully. This course focuses on developing all the four skills - speaking, listening, reading and writing as well as vocabulary building and improving grammar. After completing the course, the students are supposed to have a good knowledge and understanding of a wide range of skills and functions of the language. They are expected to have a fully operational command of the language and be able to handle complex argumentation.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completion of the course, students have mastered the skills required to take the Advanced Estonian Language Test (C1). Speaking C1: students can give clear and detailed descriptions on a wide range of topics related to personal experiences, they can develop a clear argument, expanding and supporting their points of view and comparing different viewpoints. Writing C1: students can write clear, detailed texts on a variety of topics, write a report or an essay using a variety of sentence types. Listening C1: students can understand the main ideas of long and complex speech in standard language, listen critically, draw conclusions and recognize indirect sociocultural implications. Reading C1: students can read long and complex texts for different purposes (newspapers, overviews, instructions), using appropriate reference sources and reading strategies.
